  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Narrative_EnterpriseShapePrimaryFocus> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_EnterpriseShapePrimaryFocus> ;
    narr:childCount "7"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """On 2026-04-21 Scarlet applied [Tony's additive-vs-incremental test](narr:Claim_EnterpriseShapeTentativePriority) to her funnel and tentatively named the the enterprise customer-shape as primary focus — explicitly Notion-level conviction, not a decision. The hub reframes [\"enterprise shape\"](narr:Claim_EnterpriseShapeEngagementPattern) as an engagement pattern (internal expert as bottleneck + stakeholder access), not org size — so a 5-person practice and a 150-person consultancy qualify alike. The corollary move: [expertise-distributor archetypes are deprioritized](narr:Claim_ExpertiseDistributorDeprioritized) to a secondary, keep-warm track until the primary track closes 2-3 deals. A [cohort question](narr:Claim_CohortDiagnosticForProspects) becomes a qualification diagnostic for deployment architecture. The framing carries its own check: [explicit validation and rejection criteria](narr:Claim_EnterpriseShapeValidationCriteria) gate promotion to decision, and an [earlier convergence-in-one-week finding](narr:Claim_EnterpriseCustomerARBConvergenceSpeed) (2025-07-15) is flagged as sample-of-one. Throughout, Scarlet keeps the [sponsor-not-champion risk](narr:Claim_SponsorNotChampionYouAreChampion) live — the customer's chief architect is an ally, not someone who'll ram it through.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_CohortDiagnosticForProspects> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeEngagementPattern> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeTentativePriority> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeValidationCriteria> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseCustomerARBConvergenceSpeed> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ExpertiseDistributorDeprioritized> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_SponsorNotChampionYouAreChampion> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Conviction is tentative (Notion-level) — needs validation with 2-3 more the enterprise customer-shape prospects before moving to decision." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeTentativePriority> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "if the only evidence is one pilot with a lukewarm champion (the customer's chief architect is sponsor, not champion), this may be rationalization." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeTentativePriority> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "'Enterprise shape' should be read as the engagement pattern — internal expert as bottleneck + stakeholder access — rather than as enterprise-only org size." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeEngagementPattern> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Expertise-distributor archetypes (a beta user from outside tech, a founder beta user, a collaborator, an engineering manager at the customer-as-course-creator) are relatively incremental for their users and should be deprioritized as primary sales targets." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ExpertiseDistributorDeprioritized> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "the customer's chief architect is interested, but he's not. He may be like ally, but I wouldn't say he's necessarily a champion." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_SponsorNotChampionYouAreChampion> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "3+ the enterprise customer-shape prospects fail to convert via process sale within 90 days" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeValidationCriteria> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The cohort question is now a qualification diagnostic for deployment architecture decisions." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_CohortDiagnosticForProspects> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The author flags her own focus as possibly rationalization — sample of one (the enterprise customer) plus a lukewarm sponsor, not a champion." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeTentativePriority> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_SponsorNotChampionYouAreChampion> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "Deprioritization is explicitly reversible: if 2+ expertise-distributor prospects convert at higher rates, the rejection criteria fire and the primary focus flips." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ExpertiseDistributorDeprioritized> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseShapeValidationCriteria> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The cohort diagnostic can steer prospects away from this shape entirely — toward MCP for power users or chatbot for customer-facing/AI-skeptical staff." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_CohortDiagnosticForProspects> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The most novel supporting evidence (one-week convergence) is dated 2025-07-15 and self-labeled sample-of-one, weaker than the 2026-04-21 framing it underwrites." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_EnterpriseCustomerARBConvergenceSpeed> ] ;
    narr:writer "claude (subscription)" .
